2. OpenBand source code (separate private repositories)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The source code for the OpenBand mobile apps, macOS gateway app,
gateway daemon, exit-server configuration, and supporting tooling
is **proprietary** and **all rights reserved**.

Copyright (c) 2026 OpenBand Project. All rights reserved.

This source code is not published. No license is granted to use,
copy, modify, distribute, reverse-engineer, or create derivative
works of the source code. Possession of any portion of the source
code without explicit written permission from the copyright holder
is prohibited.

Pre-launch, we have deliberately chosen to keep the implementation
closed because the project is small, copy-risk is high, and the
trust signals we offer to users (published threat model, published
protocol specs, planned independent audit) do not require
source-availability.

**Independent security researchers and formal auditors** may request
read-only access under NDA by emailing the project owner via the
contact listed on https://www.openband.io. We welcome adversarial
review and will work in good faith with anyone who signs the
confidentiality agreement.

Post-launch, once the security posture matures and a sustainable
funding model is in place, we may migrate to a source-available
license (for example, a Business Source License or PolyForm
Noncommercial) that makes the code readable and auditable without
granting commercial-reuse rights. This is a plan, not a promise.


